OL,6,FIf you believe that broadcasting is a
OL,7,Fpublic service ` not simply a
OL,8,Ftransactional relationship between a
OL,9,Fbusiness and its customers which can
OL,10,Fbe left to market forces alone ` and
OL,11,Fthat a well-funded BBC is at the
OL,12,Fcentre of the system, it is time to
OL,13,Fmake your voice heard.
OL,15,FThe judge and jury must always be the
OL,16,Fquality of the BBC's programmes and
OL,17,Fservices.
