OL,4,CBBC
OL,6,FIs the BBC somehow navigating that
OL,7,Fnarrow path which makes it distinct
OL,8,Ffrom commercial broadcasters and the
OL,9,Fniche public broadcasters in some
OL,10,Fother countries.
OL,12,FThe BBC is not simply there to address
OL,13,Fmarket failure. It is there to provide
OL,14,Fhigh quality, British services which
OL,15,Ftreat audiences as citizens ` not
OL,16,Feyeballs to deliver to advertisers or
OL,17,Fcustomers who gladly pay subscriptions
OL,18,Ffor the things they already know they
OL,19,Fwant.
